The first step is to recognize that $\mathbf{w} \cdot (\mathbf{w} \times \mathbf{u}) = 0$, hence $||\mathbf{w}|| = ||\mathbf{v}|| - ||\mathbf{w} \times \mathbf{u}||$. Squaring yields $||\mathbf{w}||^2 = ||\mathbf{v}||^2 + ||\mathbf{w} \times \mathbf{u}||^2$. On the other hand, $||\mathbf{w} \times \mathbf{u}||^2 = ||\mathbf{w}||^2 - (\mathbf{w} \cdot \mathbf{u})^2$. Since $\mathbf{u}$ and $\mathbf{v}$ are unit vectors, this implies
\[||\mathbf{w}||^2 = ||\mathbf{v}||^2 + ||\mathbf{w}||^2 - (\mathbf{w} \cdot \mathbf{u})^2,\]which simplifies to $(\mathbf{w} \cdot \mathbf{u})^2 = ||\mathbf{v}||^2 - ||\mathbf{w}||^2$.[asy]
